g.text: Game Design Documents (GDD for short) serve both documentation

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: (archiving the game development process) and a communication tool

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: (games, even the smallest ones, are rarely made by one person). It

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: is referred to as a 'living document'. It serves as core part of

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: game development pipeline, and is responsible for keeping everyone

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: on the same page.

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji
Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: My design document acts primarily as a communication tool with

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: relevant stakeholders. The canvas format is more appealing than a

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: endless pages of .pdf document. The zooming-in and out function

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: allows the stakeholder to jump back and forth from different

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: sections, allowing people to freely focus on points of interests.

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji
Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: As briefly shown in the 'Similar Games' section, there is a

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: precendent for games that require intense concentration, explore

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: heavy themes and are primarily puzzle-based. What all the indie-

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: games have in common is a capivating story and aesthetically

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: pleasing art.

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The process of creating a story for this game has been very similar

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: to writing a mystery novel i.e. excrutiatingly painful. Alongside

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: learning the technical skills of pixel art and coding a game,

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: having a playable demo was beyond the scope of this capstone

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: timeline.

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji
Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: I conceived this with the indie-game publishing house, No More

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Robots in mind (based in Manchester, UK). They published a game

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: called Not Tonight, which dealt with topics of Brexit and

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: immigration control.

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji
Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Ultimatley, the main aim of this game is use gamification

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: principles to make knowledge accessible. The medium is the message,

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: and the medium of games removes the emotional baggage related to

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: themes of climate justice, climate anxiety (and depression) and

text.font-family: Comic Shanns, monospace, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: eco-jurisprudence by providing a sandboxed environment.
